Reconciliation Defect Investigation Report (Sample Test Case)
Executive Summary

A defect was identified during reconciliation testing involving time-based metrics. Count-based metrics reconciled successfully, while duration-based metrics reported significant mismatches despite the underlying source data appearing to match after aggregation and unit conversion.

Investigation indicates that:

Record counts aggregate correctly.
Millisecond-to-second conversion works correctly.
Source B contains multiple rows per key that should be summed.
The reconciliation output appears to compare against the final row value rather than the aggregated total for certain duration metrics.
